{
  "stem": "2723.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And really, naive as we were, we thought father would be away for a few weeks and come back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That, of course, never happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father went to Palestine and stayed there through the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My mother was very, very intelligent and very educated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I don't think she was a great survivor in the sense that she was not prepared for this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it took a lot of advice from very close relatives, and devoted relatives, to help her through this very difficult initial period, which was made more difficult because we had to leave our original home, simply because there were only three of us, and there was a colossal shortage of accommodation.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I must say that looking back, the house we lived in had six apartments.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were in every one of them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were shunted from one to the other until finally we left that and went to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The continuous changes and moving within that building kept my mother frantically, frenetically busy and exhausted.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she was one of those parents who did her utmost to keep her children shielded at all times.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So really, I still could continue a kind of life, although my father was away, and although the clouds were pretty obviously gathering, and my mother knew that not being economically of any use to the country, she would be in trouble once some heavy persecution started.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she and others were aware of the annexation and end of Austria.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I wasn't-- or maybe I didn't want to be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Numbers is something I'm not particularly reliable on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think there were 60,000.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I'm not absolutely sure.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
